finition 1</dd>\n<dt>Term 2</dt>\n<dd>Definition 2a</dd>\n<dd>Definition 2b</dd>\n</dl>\n<h3 id=\"abbreviations\"><a class=\"header-anchor\" href=\"#abbreviations\">Â¶</a><a href=\"https://github.com/markdown-it/markdown-it-abbr\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Abbreviations</a></h3>\n<p>This is <abbr title=\"Hyper Text Markup Language\">HTML</abbr> abbreviation example.</p>\n<p>It converts â€œ<abbr title=\"Hyper Text Markup Language\">HTML</abbr>â€, but keep intact partial entries like â€œxxxHTMLyyyâ€ and so on.</p>\n<h3 id=\"custom-containers\"><a class=\"header-anchor\" href=\"#custom-containers\">Â¶</a><a href=\"https://github.com/markdown-it/markdown-it-container\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Custom containers</a></h3>\n<div class=\"warning\">\n<p><em>here be dragons</em></p>\n</div>\n<hr class=\"footnotes-sep\">\n<section class=\"footnotes\">\n<ol class=\"footnotes-list\">\n<li id=\"fn1\" class=\"footnote-item\"><p>Footnote <strong>can have markup</strong></p>\n<p>and multiple paragraphs. <a href=\"#fnref1\" class=\"footnote-backref\">â†©ï¸</a></p>\n</li>\n<li id=\"fn2\" class=\"footnote-item\"><p>Footnote text. <a href=\"#fnref2\" class=\"footnote-backref\">â†©ï¸</a> <a href=\"#fnref2:1\" class=\"footnote-backref\">â†©ï¸</a></p>\n</li>\n<li id=\"fn3\" class=\"footnote-item\"><p>Text of inline footnote <a href=\"#fnref3\" class=\"footnote-backref\">â†©ï¸</a></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n","prev":{"title":"æ¯”è¼ƒé…·ç‚«çš„è¨ˆé‡æ¢","slug":"android-progress-bar"},"next":{"title":"HackMd èªæ³•æ¸¬è©¦","slug":"HackMdTest"},"link":"http://yoursite.com/post/MarkDownItTest/"}